social_posts.post_text: “No Rest for the Wicked“: Finally had a nice tracing day finishing up some freelance and continuing my work on my “Queer Animals” series of anthropomorphic jockstraps! I just finished the *Piggy* one (seen still unfinished here) and am working on the *Pup* one next! Now to find some models….if anyones interested DM me!!!

“Electra Descending“: Happiest Birthday to my ultimate muse and forever inspiration @johanna_constantine !!!! Always obsessed with your Xenomorphic silhouette and insectile ways and your constant support of me and my work means so much to me! You make my vision complete!!! 🖤🖤🖤

“Golden Lights”: {SOLD!} Somewhere under the dome of stars in the paragon of animals there you shine like a star on the earth””: This sacred Heart necklace is made from various lengths and thicknesses of golden chain, and in the center a Sacred heart complete with a locket opening to store a photo, a lock of hair or whatever token you’d like!!! DM me if you’re interested! 
🔥
❤️

“Homo Sweet Homo“: How i usually # explain when asked about where I live…it’s an ever changing , ever growing coral reef of memories new and old, mine and others pulsating in a Quiet cacophony of dust and desire…decrepit books like papery leaves pile in every corner and trinkets and trash are treated like saints and sit royally under  glass cloches….

“In a Rage”: (this piece has been remixed) Your lovely obsidian horns stretch towards heaven in defiance of an absent God : this neckpiece is made from vintage plastic beads, a springbok horn and a vintage grey chandelier crystal!!! DM me if you’re interested! 🖤🖤🖤

“Twist of Shadows“: While digging through my *archives*  last night I found this photo of me circa ‘94/95(?) with my Lydia Deetz/Barnabas Collins bangs!!! I’m also serving my patented “ok hurry up and take the photo then leave me alone” face!!! Bonus points to anyone who can tell me what McDonald’s I’m in!!! ( @misscliche and @blackstiletto are exempt because I know they know!!!) also I miss that floor length leather trench coat from Domseys!!! It was $10!!! 🖤🖤🖤 {see also:GINORMOUS 90’s nose ring!!! Paging @gigilms !!!}

“Turn to the left!”: I had the extreme pleaaure of perusing (and trying on) some amazing works of art at @kasuri_ny in Hudson in their new location!!! I also got to see one of my best ghouls @motionrotation who now works there!!!! From @viviennewestwood to @waltervanbeirendonckofficial , @commedesgarcons and @yohjiyamamotoofficial and beyond, they have got it all!!! Johnathan has curated a creative and colossal shop and you MUST stop by if you’re in the area!!! Thank you for letting me play, especially in that @rickowensonline piece!!! 🖤🖤🖤

“Fear of Ghosts”: {SOLD} And the further I get from the things I care about, the less I care about how much further away I get…”: I just made this lonely little ghost out of the most perfect clear glass swirled with ectoplasmic white!!! Perfect to haunt a window or even just somewhere in your place! Handmade by me!!! DM me if you are interested! {lyrics by the Cure}

“Mrs Regera Dowdy”: Grey, grey your garden grows but in the winter no-one knows, When the Spring comes with the sun, your secret will frighten everyone…: This is my newest doll purse and the largest one to date!!! Using the beautiful vintage needlepoint purse I attached vintage composite dolls arms and legs, a large googly eye with handmade felt features and lashes, I added a velvet ribbon trimmed with vintage ribbon by me, black vintage trim and shoes and socks also handmade by me!!! The initial purse measures 13” wide by 10 1/2 tall {plus the legs 20”!!} the interior is faux black leather and has one zipper pocket!!! DM me if you’re looking to adopt!!!

“Solo” Sometimes when I’m alone or stressed I sing little songs to myself out loud….things I made up or other words for existing songs…usually pretty loudly and sometimes under my breath in public…sometimes even songs I made up during childhood with my brother or just nonsense string of consciousness lyrics to have something to focus on other than whatever is bothering me…..sometimes I really get into it and if I’m alone will often be very loud….I especially love doing this when I working on my pieces…anyone else do this?!?!

“Dusk and Desire”: As you walk home in the rain down a familiar street you realize sometimes the memory is better….” This neckpiece is made from vintage plastic and metal chain on a faux leather strap, and a from a vintage plastic Invisible Man femur bone dangles a large silver  crucifix with black enamel inlay!!! DM me if you’re interested 🖤🖤🖤

“Diadem”: A few weeks ago I walked out of my apartment to find a beautiful leaf crown just outside my door and it was so beautiful I suddenly realized this is the head tattoo idea I’ve been waiting for! And then just that week @jdraven announced they would be at @truehandsociety doing a residency again and all the pieces fell into place!!! Jamie did such a wonderful and caring job, every detail, nuance and placement was thought out plus it’s just wonderful to spend time and talk to them!!! So thank you Jamie for being so special and for bestowing on me my diadem of wilting leaves, hopefully it will give me strength in the upcoming year and beyond! 🖤🍂🖤

“Sphinx & Snakeskin”: On Sunday I took a road trip with @foca71 and @mizcandymann to the grand Re-Opening of the @bloodmilk space @sphinxandsnakeskin !!!! The space is so magickal and hosted so many amazing events (including my fashion show) it was fantastic to see it open its doors once again and rise  like a Phoenix from the ashes!!! While we were there we also took a side-trip to @anastaciasphilly which is also a beautiful magickal place!!! We got lost in all the amazing antiques for awhile before we returned!! Then to round the night off we ended up at the talented and sweet @adam_wallacavage’s beautiful home!!! Filled with his art and the art of others it’s a kaleidoscopic fantasy somewhere between peewees playhouse and the Addams family mansion!!!! Thank you so much Philly we always have so much fun when we visit you!!! And a special thank you to Jes from @bloodmilk , S&S means so much to me I’m so glad it’s back and I can’t wait to do something special there once again!!! 🖤🖤🖤 (last photo of Adam by @mizcandymann)

“Stitch in Time”: On Friday after my tattoo I got to visit the studio of my amazingly talented friend @matthew.addonizio !!! He creates clothing and fiber art sewing pieces of fabric together in a precise geometric way that if you know anything about sewing you will understand how complex the pieces and the patterns he creates are!!! Not only was it great to see his workspace but also to walk away with a piece of my own! This beautifully over sized shirt-dress!!! It’s so comfortable and stunning I may never take it off! Thank you Matthew for opening up your studio and letting me take a look around!! Please check out his work!!!🖤🤍🖤🤍

“Fear of Ghosts”: Just finished up a Foursome of spooky ethereal stained glass ghosts! Two are more clear glass with white swirled in and two are white and grey swirled glass and all with chains to hang from your wall or in your window! DM me if you want one (or more) to haunt your place! 👻👻🤍🤍👻👻

“Under the Sea” Not everything I make is specifically Ooky-spooky! I made this seahorse commission for @aquartertotwo to give to @motionrotation for the HoliGays! He wanted a man oceanic blue-green color scheme so I combined three different glasses and added some wire in the fins for some extra detail! I’m enamored with it! (And so we’re they!!) If YOU want your own commission just DM me and we can discuss design and price!!! 🧜‍♂️💚💙🧜‍♂️

“We Don’t Need Another Hero” Sometimes when I don’t understand you I look into your eyes and I KNOW…: This neckpiece is made from a vintage repurposed chain belt with gold and  faux tortoise shell rings, a Springbok horn and a hoop with gold metal fringe! Fully adjustable length! DM me if you’re interested!!!!🖤🖤🖤

His script is you and me, boy
Time, he flexes like a whore
Falls wanking to the floor
His trick is you and me, boy
Time, in quaaludes and red wine
Demanding Billy Dolls
And other friends of mine
Take your time
The sniper in the brain, regurgitating drain
Incestuous and vain

Oh, well, I look at my watch, it says nine twenty-five
And I think "Oh God, I'm still alive" 

{Bowie}

“Me, Myself and I” Dissected and disrupted, exploded all over the hotel desk and split into specific genres and sub-genres…the whole is the sum-of its parts and the parts are their own constellations in my Universe! Have accessories will travel! This is my new favourite thing to do when I travel!

“Scary Monsters, Super Creeps”: Sometimes when you go through a lot with someone the friendship changes into family and I was blessed  to see one of my family members  this weekend! Her name is/was Bong! (And not for the reason you think) and she was one of the denizens of 125 Cleveland Ave on Staten island otherwise known as the *Dungeon Family*! We turned my parents basement into a safe haven for anyone who needed somewhere to stay, to develop and to grow… a home for wayward youth where we cried laughed and created together! We were Brilliant Creatures who drew and sewed and wrote late into the night , haunting 24 hour supermarkets , living on Slurpees and reading magazines in CVS’s looking like rag dolls from nightmare land , cackling like hyenas all the way!!! Bong and I have stayed in touch all this time (almost 30 years) and when we get togther it’s like no time has passed and we talk and cry and LAUGH like only you can with someone who’s seen you go through as much as we have!!!! Two days later and my stomach STILL hurts from laughing and my heart is still full from being able to be around family again! And most importantly remember though we look somber and oh so GAWTH on our photos (which we RE) we are just two dumb idiots laughing dumb shit until we can’t breathe!!! 🖤🖤🖤 (photos circa 91/94-ish)

“Make Believe”: (these photos are from SEPTEMBER and I finally am posting them!!!) I took myself to the @david_lachapelle retrospective at @fotografiska.newyork a few MONTHS ago and was delighted to be immersed in his neons tinted, over the top, campy, sexy world! I fell in love with his chaotically sexy work in the 90’s when it was everywhere and injected fashion photography with surrealism, sexuality and most importantly CAMP!!! It was serious and didn’t take itself too seriously!!! I especially remember seeing his work in Details magazine and every shoot was just Brilliant and most of them made it on to collages on my walls!!! He also played into the  intense celebrity worship at the time and helped push their boundaries and elevate some of them to God-like status!!! It was funny and perfect and silly and nostalgic and even got me emotional a few times! Tomorrow is the last day of the exhibit but if you find yourself in NYC you should go for sure and see the spectacle for yourself !!! 💖💖💖

“Yo, Little Brother”: This weekend i got to see my brother @tiegamemnon , who I don’t get to see too often and we spent the day today walking around the city! He and I have always been pretty close (he even dressed as me for a Halloween one year) and although he moved to Minnesota making it a bit tougher to see him (and his family) and although we are sartorially very opposite we have things in common , especially humor!!! It’s nice to be able@to get together after sometimes too much time and still be able to hang out and laugh!!! We didn’t get a picture together this time but here is a photo of us sometime in the late 80s when he was going to Hungary for an exchange program!!! He is serving you a very “Growing Pains”  look and I am giving you Miss Clairol CVS dye-job GAWTH!!! Great to see you Brother!

“Mary,Mary, Quite Contrary”: Wandering though your garden in a dizzy haze, the sunshine and dragonflies harmonize….: A more medium sized *Dolly Bag* from me! (8” h by 7” w) this embroidered bag is embellished with vintage composite dolls arms and legs (with original socks and shoes!) and off while silk ruffle, a googly eye (with felt anatomy) and a bouquet of vintage faux flowers! A silver chain is the handle (7”) and the interior is faux leather! Please DM me if you’d like to adopt!

“Close One Sad Eye “: {SOLD!} She turned around one last time and mouthed the words “i finally remember” and then evaporated slowly into the rolling fog…: Large jabot made with a beautiful sheer silk chiffon scarf fashioned into a bow with a tin-type at the center and surrounded by beautiful black crochet lace trim! The jabot ties in the back with black ribbons and  can be worn tighter or looser to your liking! DM me if you are interested in purchasing it!!! 🖤🖤🖤

“ “: I went for a second time to see the @muglerofficial exhibit at the @brooklynmuseum and it was just as inspiring! I focused a lot on the small details, the insane amount of beading, the cut-outs and peek-a-boos and the jewelry and heels! Those are the kind of things that make Mugler, Mugler and that’s exactly why I love  his work! The first shot is a detail one of me and MY love of detail, and the rest are some of my fave details and some shots that didn’t make it in my other two posts! Special thanks to @ironingmaiden for inviting me along on the family outing!!! And if anyone else wants to go back to the exhibit let me know!!! 🖤🖤🖤

Up, up, up to Heaven
Up, up, up forever” : {To the Sky”, the Cure}

“Skin Show”: Last night I got to see the stunning work of @romerdanart at the @sohoprojectspace!!! Traversing through the fabulous and sweaty crowd I finally got to see Dans artwork in person! Quick strokes of color define an arched back or a chisled jawline , a magazine cut out of lace make a mustache , splatters of paint suggest cheat hair…everything is gestural and active and lovely and erotic! The brushstrokes and use of color make the images radiate joy and I wanted to take so many of them home with me! If you have a chance go experience them in person for yourself!

“Mohair Locker-room Pin-up Boys! “: I made this piece for myself originally but I figured I’d offer it up! This brooch is made from a vintage frame filled with a Tom of Finland illustration from a vintage *Physique Pictorial* hanging from a vintage Oddfellows type pin and  bouillon fringe! DM me if you’re interested!!! (Thanks @valerieperryraskin for the pin and fringe!) 🖤🖤🖤

“Butch Queen“: I made this custom jock for @lonewolfmidwood because of his obsession with flannel!!! But I think I may end up making more of these to sell (and custom ones for anyone interested!!) *Up-cycled* from a vintage flannel I thrifted,the color and pattern options are ENDLESS!!! For me, the best part is the buttons work for *easy access* {wink}!!! DM me if you’re interested in one of your own!!!
“Blood Countess“: The night is long and the burgundy flows freely…: This necklace is made from a handmade stained-glass cross and vintage chain and faux pearls! DM me if interested!

“Show Me Your Teeth“: It’s so strange how smiling in photos seems so unnatural to me , I smile often in real life and I LOVE to laugh but I after years of trying to look *cool* or *brooding* smiling seems strange….but as I get older I’m embracing it and the other changes aging brings…so thank you @demainny for snapping this shot of me (at @romerdanart art opening!)

“The Best Costume for Today”: HAPPIEST BIRTHDAY to my Aqueerious sister @motionrotation !!!! She’s ALWAYS  there for me and texts me good morning every damn day with no fail!!! She is a ride and die bitch and is always there for a good time and a good meal!!! Thank you for bringing so much joy and laughter in my life! I hope you have the best day LaDo!!! 🖤🖤🖤 (photo by @heygeorgem !!!)

“Tangled Webs”: Things have been feeling very off lately so I’m trying to focus on small things and improving my apartment so I can at least feel comfortable at home, so I’ve been doing some small redecorating like adding lighting or rugs just to make things look more cozy! Sometimes it’s the little things that help the most…

“Strange as Angels”: Happy (slightly belated) Birthday @gigilms!!! We haven’t seen each other in awhile but we HAVE known each other for an eternity and here is proof! No this isn’t a tintype it’s a photo I took on my phone of a color photocopy of an actual photo, THAT’S how old we are!!! Love You!!! Maggie and Hopey 4 EVA!!!! 🖤🖤🖤 PS. IF you’re eve wondering , why yes, that *halo* around us is one (or both) of our blood THAT’S how Goth we were!!!!👻👻👻

“McQueen is Dead, Long Live McQueen!” I’ll never forget 13 years ago I was on a ladder at work and @thegypsetter yelled to me across the store that  @alexandermcqueen had died and the world lost a true creative force…. He was one of the biggest and constant inspirations in my creative life and his work still resonates with me and always will!!! Thank you for baring your soul and for making the world more beautiful 🫀🫀🫀

“Blame Judy!”: Happiest Birthday to one of my biggest influences @judyblame !!!!! Ever since I saw his work in @i_d I was OBSESSED! His mud-larking ways have permeated how I work AND how I look/scavenge for supplies!!! A TRUE innovator and original he turned the most simple objects (like safety pins and buttons) into items of excess and glamour!!! I’m so glad I got to meet you for the brief moment I did and your words of encouragement and your messages mean the world to me still!!! You are greatly missed but always celebrated!!! Happy Birthday and thanks for everything!!!🧷🖤🧷

“Saint Judy”: In the liminal space between his beginning and his end ,  I decided to get a portrait of the amazing and inspirational  @judyblame!!!! (Also as a pre-birthday tattoo!!) Naturally @glossylandnyc was the only one I could imagine doing this… I found the perfect portrait and for him on my leg near my tattoo Glossy did of @scarlett_styleicon so they can be neighbors!!! Now he will forever be with me (or rather on me) and a constantly reminder to keep creating!!! Thank you again Glossy!!! 🖤🧷🖤 (based on an original photo by @sheila_rock_photographer !!!)

“A.L.T.”: “People love fashion exhibits because they can fantasize. They can respond to a dress, even if they can never wear a dress like that.” So Lucky I got to go to the last day of the showing of the @andreltalley pieces at @christiesinc in NYC!!! To say I was overwhelmed is an understatement I’m still gob smacked by the sheer glamour and good taste of it all!! What a beautifully amazing collection of clothing and art and artifacts!!! I was completely blown away and didn’t take as many photos as I’d like to but this really only touches the surface of what they had there!!!! Better than any museum exhibit I’ve seen recently this collection really shows a person that lived an truly innovative and amazing life!!!! And I wanted it all!!!! GIVE ME ALL THE ROBES AND KIMONOS!!! A larger than life exhibition for a larger than life person and a TRUE ICON!! 🖤🖤🖤 (more photos in my stories!!!)

“51”: This old Queen just wanted to thank you all for making me feel VERY loved all day,  something I really needed this year more than others…. All your posts and messages really warmed my cold Carvel Cake heart!!! Thank you all for making this last trip around the sun an amazing one!!! 🎂🖤🎂

“MOTHER “: I just wanted to say Happy Birthday to my amazingly inspiring Mother!!! My original muse , her creativity knows no bounds and neither does her sartorial choices!!!! When I grow up I want to be just like her!!! Mamas Boy until I die!!! I hope she has the amazing day she deserves!!! 🤍🎂🤍

“Life in Tokyo”: Still one of my fave looks from my fave party!!! Short lived but greatly loved it was a celebration of my obsessions with the Blitz, New Romantics , 80’s London , the Cha Cha Club, New Romantics, New Wave, Glam and al the music that came from  and influenced that era!!!
“Is He…You Know…” Big glasses, big  prints , big bracelets and big necklaces, big rings big emotions, big disappointments , big appetite, big belly, big ideas, big dreams 🖤🖤🖤

“UNDEAD“: I had the utmost pleasure of seeing *VAMP* by @switchnplay at @lincolncenter this past Friday and Saturday!!! A Vampire themed show featuring drag and burlesque and combos of both and things on the fringes full of dark and sexy delights!!! As a lifelong Vampire lover this was a perfect night for me!!! Every act was entrancing and sexy and left me wanting more!!! My arms hurt from snapping and my throat hurts from yelling and my shrivels black heart grew two sizes but it was well worth it!!! Everyone was AMAZING and I’ll post more in my stories since I can’t post more than 10 photos but it was a special delight to FINALLY meet my friend @vandervonodd in person!!!Thank you for an amazing night(s) and check out @switchnplay next time they have a show, I’m exhausted from the ECSTASY!!! 🫀🫀🫀

“Gazing Into the Abyss“: As a creative person sometimes you lose that spark and the muse eludes you and the bucket that comes out of the well is empty and right now I’m teetering on the precipice…So I’m actively seeking out inspiration and trying to not be so hard on myself and trying to stay calm and to understand that (hopefully) this too shall pass….

“Fresh is the Word”: Today I went to the newest exhibit at @museumatfit “Fresh, Fly, Fabulous: 50 years of Hip-Hop style”!!! Being from New York Hip-Hop was a constant and Influential part of my life and a huge part of the energy and life of the city…This exhibit specifically  explores the fashion and how it influences everything from street style to couture and from NY to all over the world!!!

“From the Flagstones”: i’ve been in Philadelphia the past two days at @sphinxandsnakeskin Working on the newest window (that i will reveal tomorrow) I love walking in and seeing this mirror made by @adam_wallacavage because entering Sphinx & Snakeskin feels like going through the Looking glass!!! I love that Jes from @bloodmilk trusts me to do the window here and I love that a piece of me is always a part of her space!!!! It’s been extra inspirational this time because I’ve been feeling creatively burnt out and this trip is exactly what I needed to get me back on track!!! I’m so excited and can’t wait to show you what I’ve been working on!!! 🐍🩸🐍

“Shed your Skin”: I spent the past three days in Philadelphia the the @bloodmilk gallery/event space @sphinxandsnakeskin creating a new window for them! The snake can represent rebirth, transformation, immortality and healing! Snakes can also symbolize protection and I hope this one looks over Sphinx & Snakeskin! From the initial sketch I did after a discussion I had with Jes, through most do the steps and finally through install i incudes process photos of my creative journey, from creating the base from cardboraard, chicken wire and packing tape, to hand cutting three different scale sizes and then through install to the final piece! This piece to me represents strength and the ability to change and to evolve and to “shes your skin” so to speak!!! Thank you to Jes and everyone at Team Bloodmilk for helping me while I was there and for giving me somewhere to create! 🩸🐍🩸

“Visible”: I made myself this brooch the other day out of a plastic visible person and i thought “MAYBE this is too big to wear?”…well I was wrong!!! I rarely make things for myself and keep them but this one is MINE! (Although if YOU’D like one I could make a similar one!!!) 🦴💀🦴

“Kiss Them for Me”: SOLD!!! “It glittered and it gleamed,For the arriving beauty queen
A ring and a car,Now you're the prettiest by far”: this vintage golden cherub (plastic) is holding some gold chains and metal and pearl tassels with a large chandelier crystal and an adjustable chain at the neck! DM me if interested!!!

“Secret Key“: I'm about to turn your secret key,Like a knife balancing on your knee”: This necklace is an assemblage made with various vintage chain of varying size and a vintage gold lock! Can’t be worn tight to the neck or a bit looser! DM me if interested!!! 🖤🔒🖤

social_posts.post_text: “Adventures in Fleamarketeering: Revival”: These past two weeks at the @chelsea_flea have been packed with vendors which means more junk for me to dig through! I always like to get dressed up to dig so I premiered  my new Kieth Haring shirt {I’ve always loved Haring, his work is so quintessential NYC to me!} All in all I had a pretty good haul !!! I got a small red suitcase from @beef_stake that I turned into a *stash box* a foppish ceramic figure, a giant gold cross (that I already made into a piece) a wonderful little table and this amazing vintage plastic @duranduran bag!!! Great day, Great haul, can’t wait until next week!!!

“Right Now”: *SOLD* “You have set my soul on fire
Only you can satisfy this great desire…” This neckpiece is made from a metal *collar* covered in faux pearls, with a handmade black silk bow and a vintage clear smoky grey chandler crystal!!! Secures in the back with a clasp! DM me if you’re interested! 🖤🖤🖤

“Pearls Before Swine”: (SOLD!) Remember to rip them to shreds before the dogs tear you to pieces…: This neckpiece is made from a metal *bib* covered in faux pearls with chain *fringe* added using various types and length of vintage chain! Elegantly dramatic for nighttime or the supermarket!!! DM if you’re interested!

“Deer Monster “: As the crisp frost gives way to wet moist moss , her jaundiced eyes open for the first time in months. Me she sees the face of love…”: this neckpiece is made from a found antler, vintage plastic tour rose shell chain links and a golden faux coral charm!! Can be worn higher or lower to the neck, full adjustable length at the back! DM me if you’re interested!!! 🖤🦌🖤

“Cuts You Up“: the smell of rust is just like the smell of blood…: This neckpiece is made from an old pair of scissors, a vintage locker room key safety pin and some vintage chain! DM me if you’re interested! 🖤🧷✂️🖤

“Through the Looking-glass”: Spent the day  in Philadelphia yesterday at the first official @bloodmilk event at the newly opened @sphinxandsnakeskin !!!! It was a twofer!!! First a Botanical Fair full of vendors and magick and tea readings and then a celebration of the relocation and opening of @jdraven’s tattoo shop @endlessnightstudio !!! (What a dangerous delight to have Jamie so close!!!) It was so wonderful to be with friends , to meet new and amazing people and to take to bus once again with my best Witches @misscliche and @blackstiletto (aka the Ladies M!) to enjoy our second home in Philly!!! So excited for more to come from S&S!!!!! 🫀🐍🖤

HAPPIEST BIRTHDAY to my best ghoul @nobodysghost !!! I hope you have the best day BITCH!!! I hope it’s WIG and it SERVES and it’s  BOOTS THE HOUSE HUNTY!!! Seriously you mean the world to me and I  can’t wait to FINALLY see you after WAY TOO LONG!!! (LA IS NOT READY!!!) Thanks for everything!!! Love you ghoul!!! 🖤🖤🖤

“Mrs. Regera Dowdy”: Tender is the night, and quiet are the whispers of grief : I very rarely make things for myself and I have always wanted one of my *baby-doll purses* so THIS one I kept for myself!!! The stones were COVERED in lichens (from the proximity to the ocean) which gave everything a much more lovely & decrepit feeling! “Every Dream Home a Heartache” To me New Orleans (especially the architecture) feels like this dystopian mix of a costal town mixed with Key West, mixed with Philadelphia mixed with San Francisco mixed with quaint European charm but then also like none of those things at all!! “Chocolated Worm Syrup”:
Yesterday @mizcandymann and I visited the highly suggested @pharmacymuseum and it was all we expected and MORE!!! Upon entering , the room is filled with ornate dark wooden cabinets that are packed with elixirs and tonics, cures and causes of death, outdated medical instruments and the morbid beauty of a fully furnished sick-room!! Harkening back to a time where Yellow Fever was just as much a concern as how one could wash ones privates without being a deviant , it was very educational and informative! However, just as a purely visual experience the museum is an enticing delight for people who appreciate this kind of antiquated beauty frozen in time! We were gasping with delight the entire time and were inspired by the archaic wonders of the museum , both the building itself and the pieces housed within! The cracked plaster and crumbling brick only added to the atmosphere! And if that wasn’t enough the back courtyard was like a magical oasis that was almost to beautiful to be true!!! Like a lush secret garden holding beautiful secrets!!! I’m a city ripe with quaint crumbling beauty this museum is a MUST VISIT!!! 🪱🍫🪱

“St Roch: {part 1}: i had seen the photos and heard the rumors but nothing prepared me for the decaying majesty that was the St Roch Chapel/reliquary! St Roch is the patron saint of the sick and incurable so people leave offerings of crutches and medical braces, anatomical ex-votos , dentures, shoes and crumbling saints. The floor is littered with “thank you” tiles, handwritten notes, pennies, desperate offerings, candle wax and scattered roach wings…Every  crumbling dusty corner is filled with such aching beauty it was almost hard to focus…but I left full of inspiration and  awe! THIS was the city I wanted to see, away from the crowds in a secret hidden room tucked away in a cemetery in a chapel that was destroyed and rebuilt , rife with faith and history and magic! Special thank you to our tour guide Liz who was as informative as she was adorable! 🫀🫀🫀

“ In Memoriam“: Remember when a band tee shirt or a haircut meant potential friendship? When a pin on your lapel or a specific earring was a sartorial signifier? When music saved our lives and lyrics were scribbled in notebooks or scratched on our skin? When we pressed up against each other at sweaty shows in crumbling basements yelling our throats raw? When we danced under the neon electric strobes in former churches thick with fog and ennui? When we shared vodka from emptied hairspray bottles crammed into toilet stalls filled with erupting laughter? When we took 5 am trains and ferries and buses back to our bedsits with the cruel sunlight streaming down on a smeared mess of maquillage? Never Forget, Ever 🩶🩶🩶

So proper judging others over her tea”: This newest *Dolly Purse* is made from a vintage embroidered floral purse, small vintage children’s lace gloves (with pink ribbon and faux Pearl) , googly-eye with handmade felt eyelids, vintage plastic dolls parts (with original@shoes!) and a vintage lace *skirt*! “The  Ruffian on the Stair” : 

Madam Life’s a piece in bloom
Death goes dogging everywhere:
She’s the tenant of the room,
He’s the ruffian on the stair.

You shall see her as a friend,
You shall bilk him once or twice;
But he’ll trap you in the end,
And he’ll stick you for her price.

With his kneebones at your chest,
And his knuckles in your throat,
You would reason — plead — protest!
Clutching at her petticoat;

But she’s heard it all before,
Well she knows you’ve had your fun,
Gingerly she gains the door,
And your little job is done.” 

William Earnst Henry {as well as Joe Orton}

“Small Wonders“: I was so excited today to come home and find my two pieces of Art I got from @archenemyarts “Small Wonders” show! I got my first ever piece from the supremely talented @alexeckmanlawn !!! Shattered and torn,a multi-layered meaty maw “Shiver ll” is haunting and dangerous and I’m so excited I was able to get it! The second piece is from my amazing friend @allisonsommers (who I love and miss so much!!!) This piece is a squidgy meaty-dream called “It Came to me One Night” encased in a handmade resin frame filled with Allison’s beautiful debris!!! Now is the fun part, where I find somewhere for them to live in my apartment!!!!

“Octopussy”: 5 years ago today I made and installed this 22 foot octopus {as well as the 9 food tall watermelon in the third photoa} the project was grueling but I was so excited with how it came out it made it all worth it!!! ! I miss doing these kinds of large scale displays, maybe I’ll have the chance again soon 🫀🐙🫀

“ Saint Roch’s”: I was thinking about the trip @mizcandymann and I too to New  Orleans last year and my {and probably hers too} fave cemetery , Saint Roch’s!!! Maybe not as flashy and well-known as some of the other cemeteries in the city, however  I fell in love with it because of it beautiful graves , lovely tile work, and a life-sized stations of the cross!!! Candice  and I were lucky enough to make it inside the reliquary {and I posted those photos} but I never posted these beautiful ones of the grounds around the chapel!!! It was a white hot day and we spent a few hours walking around, even after our tour, but well worth it to behold such beauty and Magic! 🩶🪦🩶
